{"name":"sc_task","description":"Tracks tasks related to service catalog items.","summary":"In ServiceNow, the object `{sc_task}` refers to a \"Service Catalog Task.\" This object is used to manage and track tasks associated with service catalog requests within the ServiceNow platform. When a user submits a request for a product or service through the service catalog, specific tasks may need to be completed by various teams or individuals to fulfill that request. These tasks are represented by the `{sc_task}` object.\n\nKey features and attributes of the `{sc_task}` object include:\n\n1. **Task Management**: `{sc_task}` is used to assign, prioritize, and track the progress of individual tasks related to a service request.\n2. **Workflow Integration**: It integrates with workflows to automate the assignment and progression of tasks based on predefined rules and conditions.\n3. **Assignment and Ownership**: Tasks can be assigned to specific users or groups, ensuring accountability and clear ownership.\n4. **Status Tracking**: Tracks the status of each task (e.g., Open, In Progress, Closed), providing visibility into the progress of the overall service request.\n5. **Documentation and Notes**: Allows for documentation and notes to be added to each task, facilitating communication and record-keeping.\n6. **Dependencies and Sequencing**: Tasks can be set up with dependencies, ensuring that they are completed in the correct order.\n\nOverall, the `{sc_task}` object in ServiceNow is a crucial component for operationalizing and managing the fulfillment process of service catalog requests, ensuring that all necessary steps are completed efficiently and effectively.","attributes":[{"name":"parent","type":"reference"},{"name":"made_sla","type":"boolean"},{"name":"watch_list","type":"glide_list"},{"name":"sc_catalog","type":"reference"},{"name":"upon_reject","type":"string"},{"name":"sys_updated_on","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"task_effective_number","type":"string"},{"na